Governor RTochas Okorocha of Imo State has paid a courtesy visit to former president Olusegun Obasanjo at his home in Abeokuta, Ogun State. Imo state government Facebook page captured the visit. As posted on the page: “The founder and initiator of the Rochas Foundation, Owelle Rochas Okorocha paid a ‘courtesy visit to former President Olusegun Obasanjo at his Abeokuta residence. “The governor was also accompanied by Ogun State Indigenes and beneficiaries free education from Rochas Foundation College, Ibadan and cross section of Rochas Foundation Old Students Association (ROFOSA) Ibadan chapter. Gov Okorocha once served as Adviser to the then President Obasanjo on Inter-Party.” Beneficiaries of the Rochas Foundation were with Governor  Okorocha on the visit. Ongoing construction projects were also inspected by both political leaders.  